article.headline: UC Riverside 79, Hawaii 62
article.story: RIVERSIDE, Calif. (AP) -- Larry Cunningham became UC Riverside's all-time leading scorer with a 31-point performance in a 79-62 victory over Hawaii on Saturday night. Cunningham went 10-for-15 from the field, 3-for-6 from 3-point range and 8-for-8 from the line to bring his career total to 1,390 points in a game that was part of ESPN's Bracket Buster weekend. He passed previous leader Howard Lee, who scored 1,386 points for Riverside from 1969 to 1972. A pair of Cunningham free throws with 1:36 to play tied Cunningham with Lee and gave the Highlanders a 68-58 lead. Seconds later he went to the line again and broke the record with two more free throws. Severin Gates added 11 points for UC Riverside (7-17), and Cleavon Barlow and Christian Soto scored 10 apiece. Bobby Nash had 13 points and seven rebounds and Kareem Nitoto also scored 13 for Hawaii (11-14).
